meanings.definition: Not being the only one of its kind
meanings.sent1: The store sells nonunique items that can be found in many other shops.
meanings.sent2: Her nonunique dress blended in with the crowd at the party.
meanings.sent3: It's funny how his nonunique hairstyle matches his twin brother's.
meanings.sent4: The city skyline looked nonunique, lacking any standout buildings.
meanings.sent5: The nonunique pattern on the wallpaper made the room feel ordinary.

meanings.sent1: The generic brand products are nonunique and easily replaceable.
meanings.sent2: The artist's work was criticized for being nonunique and uninspired.
meanings.sent3: It's amusing how their nonunique logo closely resembles a famous brand's.
meanings.sent4: The landscape appeared nonunique, lacking any striking features.
meanings.sent5: The nonunique flavor of the dish failed to leave a lasting impression.
